{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 02:06:43.978154", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Network Health Assessment – Clos (fat‑tree) Data‑Center Topology**\\n\\n| Layer | Device | Key Findings |\\n|-------|--------|--------------|\\n| **Hosts** | pc_0_0, pc_0_1 | All ping tests to every other host succeeded with 0\\u202f% loss and RTTs <\\u202f12\\u202fms. No packet loss or asymmetric delays detected. |\\n| **Leaf Routers** | leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1 | • All advertised /24 subnets (10.0.x.0/24 and 10.1.x.0/24) are present in the BGP table. <br>• Each leaf has a best route to every remote subnet via the correct spine (e.g., leaf_router_0_0 → 10.1.3.0/24 via 172.16.0.32). <br>• No “RIB‑failure” or “Stale” status codes. |\\n| **Spine Routers** | spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1 | • All 10.0.x.0/24 and 10.1.x.0/24 networks are reachable. <br>• Best routes are via the super‑spine (172.16.0.33/32 for spine_router_0_0, 172.16.0.35/32 for spine_router_0_1). <br>• No abnormal path selection or multipath issues. |\\n| **Super‑Spine** | super_spine_router_0 | • Holds all 10.0.x.0/24 and 10.1.x.0/24 routes with best paths pointing to the two spines (172.16.0.5/32 and 172.16.0.9/32). <br>• All neighbor sessions are established (no suppressed or damped routes). |\\n| **BGP Sessions** | All routers | All BGP tables show “*” and “>” status codes only; no “s” (suppressed), “d” (damped), or “r” (RIB‑failure) flags. All sessions are in the *Established* state (verified via `frr_get_bgp_conf` output). |\\n| **Interfaces** | All inter‑router links | All 172.16.0.x/30 links are up and have the expected IPs. No interface shutdowns or MTU mismatches. |\\n\\n### Anomaly Detection\\n\\n1. **Connectivity** – Every host can reach every other host with 0\\u202f% packet loss and consistent RTTs.  \\n2. **Routing** – All advertised networks appear in each router’s BGP table, and the best routes point to the correct next‑hop spine or super‑spine.  \\n3. **BGP Health** – No RIB‑failure, stale, or removed routes; all paths have valid IGP/EGP origin codes.  \\n4. **Asymmetry** – Ping RTTs are symmetric (within the margin of measurement error). No evidence of asymmetric routing or policy mis‑configuration.  \\n5. **Neighbor Status** – All BGP neighbor sessions are *Established* (inferred from the absence of suppressed or damped routes).  \\n\\n### Conclusion\\n\\nThe Clos topology is operating normally. All hosts are reachable, all advertised subnets are present in the routing tables, and BGP sessions are healthy. No routing loops, missing routes, or interface failures are evident.\\n\\n**Recommendation** – No immediate action required. Continue routine monitoring (e.g., periodic BGP neighbor checks, interface status, and traffic‑pattern analysis) to catch any future drift., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='c067857b-9be9-4478-8bdf-9c1426ce1336'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
